    <h1>Lentil Dhal</h1>
    <p>I've been making this yummy lentil dhal recipe   since I was a teenager. It comes from Rose Elliott's cookbook <i>Cheap and Easy</i>. I've included the creamed coconut, though it also tastes great without it. You can also make this in a soup maker, which makes things even easier!</p> 
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>250g red split lentils</li>
      <li>2 medium onions</li>
      <li>1 clove garlic</li>
      <li>2 tbsp olive oil or vegetable oil</li>
      <li>1 small piece ginger (size of a Â£2 coin)</li>
      <li>1 tsp ground cumin</li>
      <li>1 tsp ground coriander</li>
      <li>1 tsp ground turmeric</li>
      <li>1/2 tsp chilli powder</li>
      <li>800ml water or vegetable stock</li>
      <li>50g creamed coconut</li>
    </ul>
    
